{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"58b58807-06a7-4b74-a03e-53f1fbf8aa5d","content":"Here's the workflow I created at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. It triggers on GitHub releases, packs your library, and pushes to NuGet — **no API key needed**.\n\n### Manual step: Register the trusted publisher on nuget.org\n\n1. Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Add a Trusted Publisher** (or configure it when first uploading your package ID)\n2. Fill in:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank)*\n3. Save\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`id-token: write`** permission lets GitHub mint an OIDC token that NuGet.org validates — no secret/API key stored anywhere.\n- **No `--api-key`** flag is needed; `dotnet nuget push` automatically uses the OIDC token when trusted publishing is configured.\n- The workflow triggers when you **create a GitHub release**, so tag your versions (e.g., `v1.0.0`) and publish a release to push to NuGet.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"73f06a5d-e448-49ce-a6e5-1eed10db1fbd","outputTokens":264,"requestId":"E422:31693D:6A37489:7296F46:6A03CD7C"},"id":"37d72c4d-7362-40e5-a54b-57a95d08799d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:01:56.696Z","parentId":"45120a90-386c-4429-a786-d53b765c747f"}
